"{\"uid\": \"theweek.com.-articles-632841-magical-thinking-americas-probrexit-conservatives\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Britons who voted to leave the European Union did so for all sorts of reasons: immigration fears, English nationalism, economic and cultural nostalgia, post-recession funk, and so on.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 183, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 40, \"end\": 45, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999996657607, \"rank\": 3.126460757551363e-10, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But many \\\"Leave\\\" voters are people who think life in Britain is getting worse year after year.\", \"from\": 184, \"to\": 278, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They are highly skeptical of modern global capitalism with its disruption, dislocation, and \\\"creative destruction.\\\"\", \"from\": 279, \"to\": 394, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But did they actually end up voting for lots more of the very globalized capitalism they seem to loathe?\", \"from\": 396, \"to\": 500, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Many conservatives on both sides of the Atlantic seem to think so.\", \"from\": 502, \"to\": 568, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Daniel Hannan, a pundit and Conservative member of the European Parliament, repeatedly argued that a U.K. free of the EU would be a greater trading nation, as well as one \\\"unshackled\\\" by EU regulation.\", \"from\": 569, \"to\": 770, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"American conservative columnist Lawrence Kudlow called Brexit a \\\"Thatcher moment\\\" that could put Britain \\\"on the pro-growth path of free-market supply-side policies.\\\"\", \"from\": 771, \"to\": 937, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Similarly, the Wall Street Journal editorial page explained that \\\"now more than ever Britain will need supply-side economic 