entence\": \"This is why Donald Trump can offer a $10 trillion tax cut plan that would need to quintuple GDP growth to break even - all with scant criticism from many leading voices on the right.\", \"from\": 2179, \"to\": 2361, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To make these post-Brexit growth arguments sound even remotely plausible, the free-market Brexiteers had to paint an overly gloomy view of the U.K. Because without the possibility of a tremendous upside, Brexit would never have been worth the risk of severe instability.\", \"from\": 2363, \"to\": 2633, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even if you doubt the potential for long-term damage - permanently slower economic growth, the disintegration of the EU - the short-term post-Brexit picture is pretty ugly.\", \"from\": 2635, \"to\": 2807, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The pound has plunged, both the Labour and Conservative parties are in turmoil, and top banks such as Goldman Sachs see a 2017 recession as likely.\", \"from\": 2808, \"to\": 2955, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not to mention that disentangling from the EU might consume British politics and policy for years.\", \"from\": 2956, \"to\": 3054, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And all for what, exactly?\", \"from\": 3056, \"to\": 3082, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.K. is not some statist, socialist hellscape.\", \"from\": 3083, \"to\": 3133, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It already ranks ninth for global competitiveness, says the World Economic Forum.\", \"from\": 3134, \"to\": 3215, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And it ranks 10th - just ahead of the U.S. - on the Index of Economic Freedom, created by the Heritage Foundation and the Wall Street Journal.\", \"from\": 3216, \"to\": 3358, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The picture the index paints of the U.K. is that of a nation well-positioned for the future:  Economic freedom has been on an upward path in the United Kingdom over the past five years.\", \"from\": 3359, \"to\": 3544, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u2026 Disciplined fiscal adjustments have helped to restore economic dynamism, steadily reducing the budget deficit.\", \"from\": 3545, \"to\": 3657, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The corporate tax has been cut from 28 percent to 20 percent.\", \"from\": 3658, \"to\": 3719, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u2026 With an effectively institutionalized legal system that enforces the rule of law and guarantees security of contracts, the U.K. is able to benefit fully from open-market policies and a relatively efficient regulatory environment.\", \"from\": 3720, \"to\": 3951, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The labor market is well developed and vibrant.\", \"from\": 3952, \"to\": 3999, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[Index of Economic Freedom]  In other words, Britain is already a relatively well-run, free-trading nation.\", \"from\": 4000, \"to\": 4107, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And now it's made a tremendous wager to maybe become a bit more efficient, to be somewhat more dynamic, to grow modestly faster.\", \"from\": 4108, \"to\": 4236, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not only have the free-market Brexiteers urged a big gamble, but the \\\"pro-growth\\\" policies they are pushing are unlikely to be particularly popular among many populists in the Leave crowd.\", \"from\": 4237, \"to\": 4425, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(Same goes for the U.S.\", \"from\": 4426, \"to\": 4449, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"version.)\", \"from\": 4450, \"to\": 4459, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Never has so much been risked for potentially so little.\", \"from\": 4461, \"to\": 4517, \"entities\": []}]}"